Description: Handmade Custom Plush Toy Manufacturer
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Handmade custom plush.  You create the design... we do the rest. Using the kid-friendly design tools on CurlyQ Cuties' website, anyone can quickly design their own unique stuffed plush toy. Children as young as 4-years-old have commissioned their own $25 made-to-order Monster designs. No sewing or crafting skills are necessary. As a customer interactively selects the color and shape of their toy's body and features, the visual representation of their design is instantly updated in the online designer.  Customers clearly see how their customized design will look before they commit to a purchase.  Founded in January 2008 by mom entrepreneur Stephanie Estrin, CurlyQ Cuties was originally an Etsy.com shop selling ready-made monsters.  After repeated requests for customized variations of her Monsters, Stephanie recognized an opportunity to provide a customer-designed made-to-order plush toy at an affordable price.  In July 2008, Stephanie launched CurlyQCuties.com. Today, CurlyQ Cuties offers several plush toy styles from Fairy-Teeth tooth fairy pillows and plush Splatopus to larger and more elaborate Monsters and Moggins.  CurlyQ Cuties even offers a 2-1/2 foot tall Custom Monster!  All products are handmade-to-order in Texas and ship in 10 days or less. CurlyQ Cuties' Monsters were seen on NBC's Today Show this past December and their Deluxe Custom Monsters recently won a 2010 Parents' Choice Recommended Toy Award.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Consumer Goods, Manufacturing

Description: My (k) Advisor guides you to your retirement happiness.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: My (k) Advisor was created with the intention of correcting a major financial epidemic that is facing many individuals and companies in America: high cost and low value services for retirement plans. The 401(k) and retirement plan industry has truly failed business owners and employees alike.  So called "advisors" leave employers holding the bag when it comes to liability and plan reviews.  They have failed the employees by not providing sound, fiduciary advice. Enter My (k) Advisor.  We provide two core services.  The first is for the business that sponsors the retirement plan.  Instead of simply selling you a packaged product plan and leaving you to your own devices, we work FOR you on an ongoing basis.  We help to manage your fiduciary risks and make the best possible plan available to your employees. Secondly we offer a high quality, web based retirement plan advisory service.  How many questions does your HR department get about your 401(k)?  Our guess is too many.  Instead of asking your HR department, they ask us. While "participant advisory services" are made available to all of our corporate clients, we also make these available to the general public.  Our proprietary algorithms gauge your level of risk tolerance, goals, and expected risk/return.  Then they construct the most effective portfolio for you based upon the funds available within your plan. But it doesn't stop there.  We become your accountability partner.  By monitoring your portfolio on a daily basis, we will notify you when we feel any changes should be made. My (k) Advisor was created to provide you with high quality, fee-only, investment services that have normally been reserved for those with hundreds of millions of dollars.  We work for you!
Industry Groups: Administrative Services, Financial Services, Professional Services

Their products are designed for multipurpose use at almost any level of education, including elementary school, middle school, high school, and college. Knowing a one-size-fits-all approach does not work, Their products have the flexibility to adapt to your individual needs. Their focus is on designing user-friendly web applications that solve the myriad of problems encountered by students, teachers, parents, and school administrators. Every day, teachers face challenges in classroom management, lesson planning, attendance and grading, event planning, and communication. Students and parents face some of the same problems, but from a different perspective. With the launch of GPA Teacher, an online solution for educators at all levels, they have successfully incorporated many crucial applications into a single lightweight package. GPA Teacher provides a comprehensive set of classroom management tools, including seating charts, automated grade books and grade-related statistics, lesson and assignment planners, attendance and discipline records, and so on. To facilitate communication with parents and students, GPA Teacher interfaces with GPA Parent and GPA Student, providing transparent access in a secure environment. In 2009, they embarked on their latest project, a complete solution for schools called GPA Network. GPA Network includes GPA Teacher, GPA Student, and GPA Parent, as well as GPA Administrator for school officials responsible for managing school and district-wide student information. Key to GPA Administrator is the ability to generate reports and analyze statistics using many slices of the data.

Innovative Extracts LLC is a 100% Veteran owned business that was founded in early 2019 by Andy Golden, Vince Golden, and Matt Sinosky. Following the passing of the Farm Bill in December 2018, which made industrial hemp and its by-products legal nationally, the group decided to grow hemp on the Golden’s organic, family farm. Having used CBD oils themselves and knowing friends and family who had their lives changed by the benefits of the product, Innovative Extracts felt passionate about selling an affordable, locally grown and processed product to help others improve their quality of life. In addition to the farming operation, the company decided to establish the first extraction and post-processing laboratory in their area. We are excited to be able to bring these products to the market! We are looking forward to making a positive impact on the lives of those who use our products!

At ASF, we celebrate the convergence of a new generation of scientists, recognizing that within each of us lies the potential to explore, question, and discover. We firmly believe that everyone has the capacity to be a scientist, to inquire about the world around them, and to contribute to the ongoing dialogue of human knowledge. Our unique approach involves curating a diverse array of events, exclusive dinners, and exhilarating competitions, all meticulously designed to foster the cross-pollination of ideas. Whether it's a thought-provoking symposium, an intimate gathering of like-minded enthusiasts, or a high-stakes competition, ASF provides a dynamic platform for individuals from various backgrounds to come together. Our business model is driven by the passion and curiosity of our participants, who eagerly engage in our offerings. We have successfully created a sustainable ecosystem by offering premium access to our events, attracting visionary sponsors, and forming strategic partnerships. This multifaceted approach ensures the continued growth of our vibrant community. In the ever-evolving landscape of the knowledge economy, ASF is not just an organization; it's a movement. We are dedicated to promoting intellectual curiosity, fostering innovation, and catalyzing positive change in the world. Through our pioneering events and collaborations, we aim to inspire, educate, and empower individuals to explore the limitless possibilities at the intersection of science, culture, and creativity.

Description: Wound Care, Tissue Engineering, Medical Device
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Developed at Stanford, our patented Xirtam3 technology is a hybrid-hydrogel consisting of a self-assembling peptide EFK8 and Poloxamer 407. In a published study1 it was shown that when combined, the constituent parts form a highly desirable nanofiber network creating a 3-dimensional structure that resembles the extracellular matrix our own bodies create to heal tissue, otherwise known as a “scaffold”.  The Xirtam3  technology anchors to viable tissue and forms a bridge for cells to translocate into the scaffold structure, designed for cell attachment and cell dispersion throughout the network, allowing cells and tissue to regenerate more effectively. Our technology can be applied in the fields of aesthetic dermatology, wound care, stem cell research, tissue engineering and more.
Founders: Angus Jackson, Attilio Di Fiore, Basil M. Hantash, William Jackson
